title: Jesse Williams and Wife Welcome Baby Boy
text:
Comments The 'Grey's Anatomy' actor and Aryn Drake-Lee have welcomed their second child since two months ago. 
It's a boy for Jesse Williams and his wife Aryn Drake-Lee. The actor's spouse gave birth to their son about two months ago. The couple named the bundle of joy Maceo, Us Weekly learns. The baby is the second child for the couple. He joins big sister Sadie. Jesse Williams met Aryn Drake-Lee when he was still working as a school teacher in New York City. The actor exchanged wedding vows with his real-estate broker girlfriend in Los Angeles in 2012 after five years of dating. They welcomed their first child in December 2013. Jesse is known for his role as Dr. Jackson Avery on ABC's medical series " Grey's Anatomy ". He also starred on " Law & Order " and " Greek ". He was last seen on the big screen in 2013 in " Lee Daniels' The Butler " as well as " Snake and Mongoose ".
